DataElement.preferredName: Match Programming Parameter Gel Warping Algorithm Use java.lang.Double
DataElement.preferredDefinition: An exact duplicate; coinciding in characteristics; similar or consistent.:A value that is passed to a routine._A computer-implemented image processing method and apparatus for normalizing gel electrophoresis images. The method includes the steps of assigning tiepoints in a reference image and in one or more object images. The tiepoints in the object image are evaluated by comparison to a corresponding tiepoint in the reference image, and the location of the tiepoint in the object image is adjusted by slight movement to a location with respect to recognizable features in both the reference and object image. Warping functions are generated and then globally optimized.:The purpose for or application or employment of something for functional or beneficial purposes._Generic value domain for a primitive java datatype that is a Double-precision floating point number (64-bit IEEE 7540).

Concepts.definition: A computer-implemented image processing method and apparatus for normalizing gel electrophoresis images. The method includes the steps of assigning tiepoints in a reference image and in one or more object images. The tiepoints in the object image are evaluated by comparison to a corresponding tiepoint in the reference image, and the location of the tiepoint in the object image is adjusted by slight movement to a location with respect to recognizable features in both the reference and object image. Warping functions are generated and then globally optimized.
